The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
		 Monday, May 10, 2004  Q amp;A				 Long-term loss
																																																																																													I have suffered long-term capital loss by selling units of mutual funds in the financial year 2003-04. For how many years can I carry forward this loss? What is the cost inflation index for fiscal 2003-04 and fiscal 1995-96?																																																																													S. K. Bose, Rourkela
																																																																																													Long-term capital loss can be carried forward for eight subsequent assessment years and can be set off only against long-term capital gains. The cost inflation index for the fiscal 2003-04 is 463 and for 1995-96, it is 281. 																																					Redemption request																																																																																															Where should I send the redemption request for Kothari Taxshield96 and IDBI I-NIT96 units? I have certain Canbonus units. Can I send them directly to Canbank Mutual Fund office for redemption or do I have to demat them and sell through brokers?																																																																													M.K.Raghavan, Guwahati
																																																																																													Kothari Pioneer Mutual Fund has been taken over by Franklin Templeton Mutual Fund and you can send the redemption request to Franklin Templeton Investments  2D and 2E, Landmark Building, 2nd floor, 228-A, A. J. C. Bose Road, Calcutta-700020. IDBI Mutual Fund has been taken over by Principal Mutual Fund and the Calcutta branch address is Block No. 503, 5th Floor, Shubham, 1, Sarojini Naidu Sarani, Calcutta-700001. It is not required to dematerialise the Canbonus units and sell them through brokers. You can send the redemption request directly to Canbank Mutual Fund. The Calcutta branch is located at 4th floor, Vaibhav, 4, Lee Road, Calcutta-700020. 																																					Homing in on home loans																																																																																															What is the maximum amount of tax rebate available on housing loan interest?																																																																													Subimal Basu, Jamshedpur
																																																																																													Repayment of housing loans, both principal and the interest, is eligible for tax rebate under section 88 up to an amount of Rs 20,000 per annum. Again, interest on loan taken for acquisition, construction, repair, renewal or reconstruction of house property is allowed as deduction under income from house property up to Rs 30,000.
	If you have any queries about investing or taxes or a high-cost purchase you are planning, mail to: btgraphabpmail.com, 
	or write to: Business Telegraph, 6 Prafulla Sarkar Street, Calcutta 700 001.
